  "text": "Acid soil associated with aluminum toxicity is a widespread problem in cereals. An extensive field study of complete and substituted triticales over diverse soils in Spain [CITATION_1] found that the main factor for yield variation was soil pH. Complete triticales outyielded substituted triticales in the majority of sites.",
